HEADWORD: Gardenia
<hw>Garde"ni*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of plants, some species of which produce
beautiful and fragrant flowers; Cape jasmine; -- so called in honor of
Dr. Alexander <xex>Garden</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

